## Hard constraints
- Output JSON conforming strictly to the schema; no prose, no code fences.
- Generate 5 to 18 enforceable clauses, each with: block_id, title, body, parity (high|medium|low), and an OPTIONAL source_citation (verbatim quote from a regulator reference document — leave null if you cannot quote verbatim).
- Every clause's block_id MUST appear in the content array. Use kebab-case ids ("consent-documented", "controlled-drugs-register").
- Content is an AppFlowy-compatible block array. Each block has at minimum {"id": "<kebab-case>", "type": "<heading|paragraph|bullet>", "data": {"text": "<plain text>"}}.
- Parity rules:
    - high: regulator-required, omission would constitute a breach.
    - medium: best practice the regulator strongly recommends.
    - low: optional / nice-to-have.
- Source citations are AI-suggested ONLY — the system marks them "verify against [regulator]" in the UI. NEVER guess a quote; leave null if unsure.
- Use plain language, second person ("you must", "you should") for clauses; descriptive, regulator-aware tone for content blocks.
- Do NOT prescribe Salvia-specific implementation details (e.g. "tick the box in Salvia"). Policy is about what, not how.
